to build docker image
docker build -t springboot-docker-demo .

to check list of docker images
docker images

to add tage to docker image and build it
docker build -t springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE .

to remove docker images
docker rmi image_id

to run a container with local tag
docker run -p 8080:8080 springboot-docker-demo

to run a container with a custom tag
docker run -p 8081:8080 springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE
http://localhost:8080/docker ==> to hit the api

to run docker container in detached mode
docker run -d -p 8080:8080 springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE

to see active containers
docker ps

for logs of a container
docker logs -f container_id

for stopping container
docker stop container_id

pushing docker image to docker hub
docker login
docker tag springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE manojhc18/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE
docker images
docker push manojhc18/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE

to pull the pushed docker image
docker pull manojhc18/springboot-docker-demo:0.1.RELEASE

for mysql image
docker pull mysql:latest

creating a new network
docker network create springboot-mysql-net

to create a new docker container for mysql in a container network
docker run --name mysqldb --network springboot-mysql-net -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=root -e MYSQL_DATABASE=employeedb -d mysql

docker exec -it container_id bash

inside bash
mysql -u root -p

check active containers
docker ps


if u can't find db container use
docker ps -a

then start that container
docker start d625cc90377c

to run the application in a specific docker netword in detached mode
docker run --network springboot-mysql-net --name springboot-mysql-container -p 8080:8080 -d spring-restful-webservices

to start docker compose in detached mode
docker-compose up -d

to stop docker compose
docker compose down


for all docker compose commands
docker compose ls
docker compose ps
docker compose config
docker inspect mysqldb


for this project============================================================================


List all volumes
docker volume ls

Identify unused volumes
docker volume ls -f dangling=true

Remove unused volumes
docker volume prune

Remove all volumes (if you want a clean slate)
docker compose down -v

for accessing mongo db
docker exec -it mongo_db mongo -u manoj -p manoj --authenticationDatabase admin

for accessing postgresql
docker exec -it ms_pg_sql psql -U manoj


to build docker compose first time
docker compose up --build
docker compose up -d --build

